rows.name: Parks
rows.description: The city began creating parks as early as 1844. Today, Philadelphians enjoy a variety of parks, from the natural wonders of the Wissahickon Valley to a tree-lined playlot down the block.

rows.name: Recreation Centers
rows.description: Our centers include gymnasiums, pools, weight rooms, basketball and tennis courts, dance and arts spaces, computer rooms, and auditoriums. Many sites offer a range of programs for people of all ages.

rows.name: Historic & Cultural Attractions
rows.description: From the Fairmount Park historic houses to the Dell Music Center, there is something from almost every era of Philadelphia’s history in our park and recreation system!

rows.name: Places to Eat
rows.description: From lunch in LOVE Park to sit-down dinners along the Schuylkill River, Philadelphia Parks & Recreation offers an abundance of diverse dining destinations.

rows.name: Older Adult Centers
rows.description: In partnership with Philadelphia Corporation for the Aging our older adult centers offer recreation, dining, educational opportunities, and more to Philadelphians 55 and over.

rows.name: Golf Courses
rows.description: Philadelphia's public golf courses have welcomed golfers for many years. With Philadelphia's parks as backdrops, each course has unique characteristics that provide a memorable experience to golfers of all skill levels.

rows.name: Ice Rinks
rows.description: In partnership with Ed Snider Youth Hockey Foundation, Philadelphia Parks & Recreation helps people of all ages hit the ice most months of the year. Activities include ice hockey, ice skating, skating lessons and open skating time.

rows.name: Boat Launches
rows.description: To explore Philadelphia on the water, access the Delaware and Schuylkill rivers at these boat launches!

rows.name: Environmental Education Centers
rows.description: Come learn about Philadelphia’s natural environment and how to preserve it. Visit one of our centers and bring your family, school, or group! Our knowledgeable staff will guide you through a wonderful educational experience.

rows.name: Recycling Center
rows.description: Philadelphians' home for free or low-cost organic material pick up and drop off.

rows.name: Horse Stables
rows.description: From race tracks to mounted park guards, horses have always been a big part of Philadelphia park and recreation history. Philadelphia horse lovers can choose from a variety of riding programs and stabling options.
